President Biden spoke with leaders from the American Jewish community to express his support for Israel and condemn the attacks by Hamas terrorists. He emphasized that there is no justification for terrorism and reiterated the administration's commitment to supporting Israel's right to defend itself. The President also discussed the efforts to bring American hostages held by Hamas back home. Following his remarks, a roundtable discussion was held with Jewish community leaders, focusing on the administration's commitment to identifying, condemning, and investigating antisemitic incidents in the U.S. The importance of vigilance against rising antisemitic actions and solidarity with the Jewish community was also highlighted. The roundtable also discussed a previous meeting held to develop the President's National Strategy to Counter Antisemitism, involving representatives from various federal agencies.